  <description type="morphology">Plants light to dark green, cespitose, crowded or rarely forming a dense turf.  Cauline leaves long-rectangular or long-elliptical to broadly lanceolate, straight to strongly reflexed, 0.5–2 mm, apex rounded to broadly acute, occasionally apiculate; distal cells sometimes 2-stratose marginally in patches or entirely and also medially in patches, distal laminal cells 7–13 µm in width, 1:1; costa subpercurrent to percurrent.  Specialized asexual reproduction absent.   Perichaetia single on an elongate axis, terminating the axis; perichaetial leaves loose and flexuose, ligulate to ovate-lanceolate, little sheathing at base, basal cells rectangular, smooth, distal laminal cells quadrate, strongly papillose.  Capsule long- or rarely short-cylindric, wide-mouthed, with flat or weakly convex exothecial cells, these usually 20–25(–30) µm wide, though somewhat bulging near the neck.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature summer–fall.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Calcareous rock in wet situations, especially near waterfalls, moist gorge walls, rarely soil;</description>
  <description type="morphology">low to high elevations (0–3000 m);</description>
